   <conbody>
      <hazardstatement id="IncorrectVoltageSettingAlwaysCheckT-F77AF2FE"
                       type="caution"
                       class="+ topic/note hazard-d/hazardstatement ">
         <messagepanel class="+ topic/ul hazard-d/messagepanel ">
            <typeofhazard class="+ topic/li hazard-d/typeofhazard ">Incorrect Voltage setting</typeofhazard>
            <howtoavoid class="+ topic/li hazard-d/howtoavoid ">Always check that the input DC voltage of the module is
correct for the systems DC voltage before installing the inverter
module.</howtoavoid>
         </messagepanel>
      </hazardstatement>
      <p class="- topic/p ">For the 24, 48 and 60 V DC input voltage inverter modules the correct
input voltage needs to be set. This is done with the DIP-switches
on the back of the inverter modules (behind the grid, placed on the
PCB).</p>
